data.name: Fiesta Veggie Burrito
data.quickTastyDescription: A vibrant and filling burrito packed with fresh vegetables and a zesty homemade salsa.
detailedCookingInstructions: In a pan, heat olive oil over medium heat. Add diced bell peppers and red onion, sauté until soft (about 5 minutes).
Stir in black beans and corn kernels, cook for another 5 minutes until heated through. Season with salt and pepper.
In a small bowl, mix diced tomatoes, chopped cilantro, lime juice, and salt to create a fresh salsa.
Warm the tortilla in a dry skillet for 30 seconds on each side until pliable.
Layer the sautéed vegetable mixture, sliced avocado, shredded lettuce, cheddar cheese, and a dollop of sour cream in the center of the tortilla.
Spoon the fresh salsa over the filling, then fold in the sides and roll tightly to form a burrito.
Serve immediately with extra salsa on the side.
data.detailedName: Fiesta Veggie Burrito with Homemade Salsa
